ecological_assessment.qualitative_description: The model has a complex implementation with many additional features beyond the basic NPZ model, but contains most core NPZ equation components with some variations

nutrient_equation_uptake.explanation: Contains Michaelis-Menten kinetics (N/(K_N+N)) with additional temperature and light scaling. Self-shading is present but implemented differently (exp(-k_w * P))

nutrient_equation_recycling.explanation: Lacks explicit recycling terms (beta*lambda*P^2/(mu^2+P^2)*Z and gamma*q*Z). Instead has detritus remineralization and temperature-dependent recycling

nutrient_equation_mixing.explanation: No explicit environmental mixing term (k*(N0-N)) present

phytoplankton_equation_growth.explanation: Contains nutrient uptake term with Michaelis-Menten kinetics, temperature scaling, and light limitation. Very similar to standard NPZ growth equation

phytoplankton_equation_loss.explanation: Contains mortality (m_P * P) and grazing loss terms. Lacks standard mixing loss term, but adds nutrient stress mortality

zooplankton_equation.explanation: Contains predation growth term and mortality term. Adds nutrient-dependent assimilation efficiency and nutrient stress mortality
